2019 Pan American Games|2019 Lima]]|[[Taekwondo at the 2019 Pan American Games \u2013 Women's 67 kg|67 kg]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Pan American Taekwondo Championships|Pan American Championships]]}}\n{{MedalGold|2008 Caguas|67 kg}}\n{{MedalGold|2016 Queretaro|67 kg}}\n{{MedalGold|2018 Spokane|67 kg}}\n{{MedalBronze|2014 Aguascalientes|67 kg}}\n| updated = 19 September 2018\n}}\n\n'''Paige Arielle''' \"'''McFierce'''\" '''McPherson ''' (born October 1, 1990, in [[Abilene, Texas]]) is an Olympic [[taekwondo]] competitor from the [[United States]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Paige McPherson competes in Olympic Games|url=http://www.sdpb.sd.gov/newsite/shows.aspx?MediaID=60886&Parmtype=RADIO&ParmAccessLevel=sdpb-all|accessdate=October 27, 2014|publisher=[[South Dakota Public Broadcasting]]|date=July 27, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{Cite sports-reference|Paige McPherson|https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/mc/paige-mcpherson-1.html|October 27, 2014}}</ref>\n\nMcPherson was a silver medalist at the [[2011 Pan Am Games]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Aldred|first1=Tanya|title=London 2012 Olympics: tragic death of parents puts defeat in perspective for Sarah Stevenson|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/olympics/taekwondo/9468098/London-2012-Olympics-tragic-death-of-parents-puts-defeat-in-perspective-for-Sarah-Stevenson.html|accessdate=October 27, 2014|publisher=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=August 10, 2012}}</ref>\n\nShe represented the USA at the [[2012 Summer Olympics]] in the [[Taekwondo at the 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 67 kg|women\u2019s 67 kg taekwondo event]] and in the preliminary round secured a surprise defeat over [[Team GB]]'s [[Sarah Stevenson]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Paige McPherson advances|url=http://espn.go.com/olympics/summer/2012/judo/story/_/id/8254721/2012-london-olympics-us-fighter-paige-mcpherson-beats-british-favorite-taekwondo|accessdate=October 27, 2014|agency=Associated Press|publisher=ESPN.com|date=August 10, 2012}}</ref> McPherson went on to win a bronze medal by defeating [[Franka Ani\u0107]] of [[Slovenia]], 8-3.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Cherwa|first1=John|last2=Dillman|first2=Lisa|title=OLYMPICS ROUNDUP Paige McPherson wins bronze in taekwondo|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2012/aug/10/sports/la-sp-oly-roundup-20120811|accessdate=October 27, 2014|publisher=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=August 10, 2012}}</ref>\n\nAfter winning a gold medal in the 2016 Pan American Games McPherson was selected to represent the United States as a member of the Team USA Taekwondo Team in the 2016 Summer Olympics in Rio, Brazil.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Zirogiannis|first1=Marc|title=The Age of McFierce|journal=Tae Kwon Do Life Magazine|date=September 2016|volume=2|issue=September 2016|pages=18\u201322|url=https://tkdlifemagazine.com/subscribers-page-current-and-back-issue/|accessdate=4 September 2016}}</ref>\n\nMcPherson grew up in [[Sturgis, South Dakota]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Holland|first1=Deb|title=Paige McPherson plans visit to Sturgis|url=http://rapidcityjournal.com/news/local/communities/sturgis/paige-mcpherson-plans-visit-to-sturgis/article_872815d4-9834-5356-a09d-6b6db7d62141.html|accessdate=October 27, 2014|work=Meade County Times-Tribune|publisher=[[Rapid City Journal]]}}</ref> She and four other siblings were adopted by Susan and Dave McPherson.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Holland|first1=Deb|title=Sturgis woman going for Olympic gold|url=http://rapidcityjournal.com/news/local/communities/sturgis/sturgis-woman-going-for-olympic-gold/article_78003514-fe3d-59e5-ba32-e52191cb68ec.html|accessdate=October 27, 2014|work=Meade County Times\u2013Tribune|publisher=Rapid City Journal|date=July 27, 2012}}</ref> Her biological family includes an older brother and two half-siblings.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Florek|first1=Michael|title=Olympic taekwondo star is one of five adopted kids in family|url=http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/sports/olympics/london/taekwondo/story/2012-06-18/paige-mcpherson-taekwondo-olympics/55688328/1|accessdate=October 27, 2014|publisher=[[USA Today]]|date=June 19, 2012}}</ref> She is of African American and Filipino descent.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Rodriguez|first1=Alex|title=Paige McPherson: She's McFierce|url=http://www.miaminewtimes.com/2012-11-22/news/paige-mcpherson-she-s-mcfierce/full/|accessdate=October 27, 2014|publisher=[[Miami New Times]]|date=November 22, 2012}}</ref> She graduated from Black Hills Classical Christian Academy in 2009 and then went on to attend [[Miami-Dade College]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Knuckles|first1=Dennis|title=McPherson ready to live Olympic dream|url=http://www.bhpioneer.com/local_news/article_0402b054-74fc-11e1-9666-001871e3ce6c.html?TNNoMobile|accessdate=October 27, 2014|publisher=[[Black Hills Pioneer]]|date=March 23, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{USOPC profile|MC/Paige-McPherson}}\n*{{Twitter |mcfierce2012|Paige McPherson}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:McPherson, Paige}}\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Abilene, Texas]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from South Dakota]]\n[[Category:African-American sportswomen]]\n[[Category:American martial artists of Filipino descent]]\n[[Category:American female taekwondo practitioners]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Olympic taekwondo practitioners of the United States]]\n[[Category:Taekwondo practitioners at the 2012 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Taekwondo practitioners at the 2011 Pan American Games]]\n[[Category:Olympic bronze medalists for the United States in taekwondo]]\n[[Category:Pan American Games silver medalists for the United States]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2012 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:People from Sturgis, South Dakota]]\n[[Category:Miami Dade College alumni]]\n[[Category:Pan American Games gold medalists for the United States]]\n[[Category:Taekwondo practitioners at the 2016 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Pan American Games medalists in taekwondo]]\n[[Category:Taekwondo practitioners at the 2015 Pan American Games]]\n", "t