y]]|date=June 19, 2012}}</ref> She is of African American and Filipino descent.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Rodriguez|first1=Alex|title=Paige McPherson: She's McFierce|url=http://www.miaminewtimes.com/2012-11-22/news/paige-mcpherson-she-s-mcfierce/full/|accessdate=October 27, 2014|publisher=[[Miami New Times]]|date=November 22, 2012}}</ref> She graduated from Black Hills Classical Christian Academy in 2009 and then went on to attend [[Miami-Dade College]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Knuckles|first1=Dennis|title=McPherson ready to live Olympic dream|url=http://www.bhpioneer.com/local_news/article_0402b054-74fc-11e1-9666-001871e3ce6c.html?TNNoMobile|accessdate=October 27, 2014|publisher=[[Black Hills Pioneer]]|date=March 23, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.teamusa.org/Athletes/MC/Paige-McPherson.aspx Paige McPherson Team USA bio]\n*{{Twitter |mcfierce2012|Paige McPherson}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:McPherson, Paige}}\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Abilene, Texas]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from South Dakota]]\n[[Category:African-American sportswomen]]\n[[Category:American martial artists of Filipino descent]]\n[[Category:American female taekwondo practitioners]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Olympic taekwondo practitioners of the United States]]\n[[Category:Taekwondo practitioners at the 2012 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Taekwondo practitioners at the 2011 Pan American Games]]\n[[Category:Olympic bronze medalists for the United States in taekwondo]]\n[[Category:Pan American Games silver medalists for the United States]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2012 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:People from Sturgis, South Dakota]]\n[[Category:Miami Dade College alumni]]\n[[Category:Pan American Games gold medalists for the United States]]\n[[Category:Taekwondo practitioners at the 2016 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Pan American Games medalists in taekwondo]]\n[[Category:Taekwondo practitioners at the 2015 Pan American 